+\alias{matrixOps.fmalloc}
+\title{Matrix algebra for fmalloc-backed vectors and matrices}
+\usage{
+\method{\%*\%}{fmalloc}(x, y)
+
+\method{crossprod}{fmalloc}(x, y = NULL, ...)
+
+\method{tcrossprod}{fmalloc}(x, y = NULL, ...)
+
+\method{matrixOps}{fmalloc}(x, y)
+}
+\arguments{
+\item{x, y}{Numeric, logical, or complex vectors/matrices. At least one
+operand must be fmalloc-backed for these methods to dispatch.}
+
+\item{...}{Unused.}
+}
+\value{
+An fmalloc-backed numeric or complex matrix.
+}
+\description{
+Provides fmalloc-aware matrix products for \code{\%*\%}, \code{crossprod()}, and
+\code{tcrossprod()}. Results are allocated in the runtime of the first fmalloc
+operand and returned as fmalloc-backed matrices.
+}
+\details{
+These methods intentionally use direct element access rather than falling back
+through \code{base::\%*\%}, so large results do not have to be materialized as
+ordinary R matrices before being copied back into fmalloc storage.
+}
